A method that changes its receiver uses `this ~Type`.

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    reset |this ~Vector2|:
        this.x = 0.0
        this.y = 0.0
    ;
]

The value must be stored in a mutable binding:

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    vector ~= Vector2(3.0, 4.0)
    ~vector.reset()
]

The first `~` makes the binding mutable. The second requests exclusive access
for this method call.

A shared method is called without `~`.
